<subsection><title>3. Write expressions to compare quantities</title>

<introduction><p>There is often more than one way to express a comparison with mathematical notation.</p></introduction>

<subsubsection><title>Example</title>

<example><statement><p>When we say that "<m>A</m> is 3 times larger than <m>B</m>," we mean that <m>A=3B</m>.</p>
</statement></example>

<example><statement><p>When we say that "<m>A</m> is 3 more than <m>B</m>," we mean that <m>A=B+3</m>.</p>
</statement></example>
</subsubsection>

<subsubsection><title>Exercises</title>

<p><ol label="a" cols="3">
    <li><m>x=5H</m></li>
    <li><m>x=\dfrac{5}{H}</m></li>
    <li><m>x=5+H</m></li>
    <li><m>H=x+5</m></li>
    <li><m>H=5x</m></li>
    <li><m>H=\dfrac{5}{x}</m></li>
    <li><m>x-H=5</m></li>
    <li><m>H-x=5</m></li>
    <li><m>\dfrac{x}{H}=5</m></li>
    <li><m>\dfrac{H}{x}=5</m></li>
    <li><m>\dfrac{\log x}{\log H} = 5</m></li>
    <li><m>\log x - \log H =\log 5</m></li>
    <li><m>\log x + \log 5 = \log H</m></li></ol></p>

<exercise><statement><p>From the list above, match all the correct algebraic expressions to the phrase "<m>x</m> is 5 times as large as <m>H</m>."</p></statement>
    <answer><p>(a), (i), (l)</p></answer></exercise>

<exercise><statement><p>From the list above, match all the correct algebraic expressions to the phrase "<m>x</m> is 5 more than <m>H</m>."</p></statement>
